Spring Boot Application:
-------------------------

1) SpringBoot Auto Configuration :----------------

The entry point for Spring Boot Application is the class contains @SpringBootApplication annotation.
This class should have the Main method to run the Application.

@SpringBootApplication contains @EnableAutoConfiguration, @ComponentScan, @SpringBootConfiguration annotation.

package com.springboot.learning 

import org.springframework.boot.SpringApplication
import org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.SpringBootApplication
@SpringBootApplication
public class DemoApplication{
  public static void main(String[] args){
    SpringApplication.run(DemoApplication.class, args);
    }
   }
   
   
2)SpringBoot Quick-start:------------------------

prerequisites are java 7 and maven 3.2
1)Spring Boot CLI (Command Line Interface) : this needs groovy file to run the Application :: spring run hello.groovy
2)Spring Boot-BootStraping : http://start.spring.io

Create an Executable Jar: 
command:  mvn clean install
it creates a jar file in the Target folder, 
run the jar file using
cmd : java -jar jarname



